Tell me how to make a platform that detects rugged solana coins
Building a platform to detect "rugged" (rug pull) Solana coins involves analyzing on-chain data for common red flags. Rug pulls on Solana typically occur when creators drain liquidity, mint unlimited tokens, freeze accounts, or bundle-snipe buys to dump on buyers. Most happen on DEXes like Raydium or platforms like pump.fun.Your platform could be a web app (e.g., using Next.js or React for frontend, Node.js/Express for backend) that takes a token mint address as input, runs checks via Solana RPC and APIs, computes a risk score (0-100, where higher = safer), and displays results with warnings.Key Rug Pull Red Flags to CheckDetect these programmatically:
  • Mint Authority: If not revoked (null), dev can mint infinite tokens.
  • Freeze Authority: If not revoked, dev can freeze accounts (prevent selling).
  • Liquidity Pool (LP): Burned/locked/renounced? Low liquidity or dev-controlled = high risk.
  • Top Holders: If top 10-20 wallets hold >20-50% supply, or are clustered (same owner), risk of dumps.
  • Bundled/Sniped Buys: Early buys by related wallets before public.
  • Metadata/Socials: Fake or missing website/Twitter; recent creation.
  • Honeypot Checks: Simulate sells to detect if trading is blocked.
  • Other: Mutable metadata, high tax fees, blacklisted wallets.
Studies show ~93-98% of new Solana tokens exhibit rug or pump-dump traits.
Tech Stack Recommendations
  • Languages: JavaScript/TypeScript (Node.js) or Python.
  • Libraries:
    • @solana/web3.js + @solana/spl-token for RPC queries.
    • Helius or QuickNode RPC (free tier for dev; paid for production).
    • APIs: Rugcheck.xyz, Solsniffer, GoPlus, Dexscreener (for market data).
  • Open-Source Starters (fork these on GitHub):

  • Frontend: React/Vue with charts (Chart.js for holder distribution).
  • Backend: Express/FastAPI; cache results with Redis.
  • Deployment: Vercel (free for web), Railway/Render for backend.
  • Real-Time: WebSocket for monitoring new pools (via Helius webhooks).
Step-by-Step: Core Detection Logic (TypeScript Example)Install deps: npm i @solana/web3.js @solana/spl-token
typescript
import { Connection, PublicKey } from '@solana/web3.js';
import { getMint, getAccount } from '@solana/spl-token';
import axios from 'axios'; // For APIs

const RPC = 'https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com'; // Use Helius for speed
const connection = new Connection(RPC);

async function checkToken(mintStr: string) {
  const mintPubkey = new PublicKey(mintStr);
  let score = 100;
  const warnings: string[] = [];

  // 1. Mint/Freeze Authority
  const mintInfo = await getMint(connection, mintPubkey);
  if (mintInfo.mintAuthority) {
    score -= 40;
    warnings.push('Mint authority not revoked (infinite supply risk)');
  }
  if (mintInfo.freezeAuthority) {
    score -= 30;
    warnings.push('Freeze authority enabled (can freeze wallets)');
  }

  // 2. Supply & Decimals
  const supply = mintInfo.supply;
  // Low supply + high holders concentration = risk

  // 3. Top Holders (via Helius API or getTokenLargestAccounts)
  const holders = await connection.getTokenLargestAccounts(mintPubkey);
  const top10 = holders.value.slice(0, 10);
  const top10Percent = top10.reduce((acc, h) => acc + Number(h.uiAmount), 0) / Number(supply) * 100;
  if (top10Percent > 50) {
    score -= 25;
    warnings.push(`Top 10 holders own ${top10Percent.toFixed(2)}% (dump risk)`);
  }

  // 4. Liquidity (Raydium via GeckoTerminal or Dexscreener API)
  const dexResponse = await axios.get(`https://api.dexscreener.com/latest/dex/tokens/${mintStr}`);
  const pair = dexResponse.data.pairs[0];
  if (pair) {
    const lpLocked = pair.liquidity?.locked; // Or check if burned
    if (!lpLocked || pair.liquidity.usd < 10000) {
      score -= 35;
      warnings.push('Low/unlocked LP (easy rug)');
    }
  }

  // 5. External APIs (Rugcheck.xyz)
  const rugResponse = await axios.get(`https://api.rugcheck.xyz/v1/tokens/${mintStr}/report`);
  if (rugResponse.data.riskScore < 50) {
    score = rugResponse.data.riskScore;
    warnings.push(...rugResponse.data.risks);
  }

  // Final
  return { score: Math.max(score, 0), riskLevel: score > 70 ? 'Low' : score > 40 ? 'Medium' : 'High', warnings };
}

// Usage: await checkToken('TOKEN_MINT_ADDRESS_HERE');
This is a basic scorer; integrate more APIs for accuracy.
